OL,3,CA peek behind the Oscars curtain: What
OL,4,Cyou don't know about the Awards
OL,6,FAfter getting the award, winners are
OL,7,Fasked to sign a contract that states
OL,8,Fthey cannot sell the prize before
OL,9,Ffirst offering it back to the Academy
OL,10,Ffor $1.
OL,12,FIf an Oscar-winner dies and passes
OL,13,Ftheir award down to their children,
OL,14,Fthey must also abide by the same rules.
OL,16,FIf the winner refuse to sign the
OL,17,Finitial contract, they are not allowed
OL,18,Fto keep it. But if the Academy does
OL,19,Fnot want it back, they can sell it to
OL,20,Fwhomever they like for whatever price.
